rComments: I've had professor Leblanc for two classes and she's genuinely very caring. If you pay attention to lectures and actually try for assignments you will get a good mark. She also gives lots of freedom for assignments so you can pick a topic that actually interests you.

Very straightforward class; professor is friendly. I would say if you're looking for an easy elective class, maybe don't go with this one. It's very useful to have a tiny bit of interest in Celtic Studies beforehand.

SUch an amazing prof! And bird course certified, one of the few course I've taken in university where the prof's goal was to make the class interested rather than the students just learning everything. Highly recommend if you want an easy A!!!!

Certified bird course. No final exam, just 2 small assignments, a group project and a final paper. Not a tough grader at all, Prof. Leblanc is exceedingly nice and wants you to succeed. You don't really get tested on anything from class because there's no exams but the material is interesting and can help you with your final paper! 10/10 recommend!

Has her own website for the course that has the readings on it. No need to buy a textbook for the course but there are a lot of readings to do online. No midterm and participation is needed. Only two assignments; one is a group project and the other is an 8 pg research paper.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor LeBlanc is amazing! Her lectures are incredibly interesting, she is so knowledgable, and truly cares about her students. Prof LeBlanc wants everyone to succeed and goes out of her way to make that happen.  Easy assignments, an easy marker, and a really cool human being.

The lack of midterm kind of bothered me, because I don't know if at the end I will be prepared for the exam. Trivia nights are fun, and the prof has a pub night once a semester which involves a lot of fun Celtic traditional music and dancing. Class is a must, otherwise you will be at a loss depending on the slides.
